# GoChul Fitness Rulebook

## 0) Mandatory maintenance policy

- Every code change or requirement change **must** be reflected in this rule file in the same PR/change-set.
- If implementation and this file diverge, implementation is source of truth short-term, then this file must be updated immediately.
- Do not introduce new API behavior, statuses, roles, or data fields without updating:
  - this rule file
  - API types in `src/app/type/api/index.ts`
  - affected route handlers and hooks

## 1) System architecture

- Framework: Next.js App Router with server route handlers under `src/app/api/**`.
- Auth: Clerk server auth in route handlers via `auth()` and user profile via `currentUser()`.
- Data layer: InstantDB admin SDK (`instantServer`) with schema in `instant.schema.ts`.
- Client data-fetching: TanStack Query hooks (`src/hooks/useContracts.ts`, `src/hooks/useHistory.ts`, `src/hooks/useUser.ts`).
- Realtime sync: Ably pub/sub with server-issued token auth via `GET /api/realtime/token`, user-scoped channels (`user:{instantUserId}`), and client cache invalidation in `src/providers/RealtimeProvider.tsx`.
- Environment gate: realtime publish/subscribe/token is enabled only in production (`NODE_ENV === 'production'`) and is intentionally disabled in local development.
- UI: Mobile-first pages under `src/app/(main)/**`, shadcn-style components under `src/components/ui/**`.
- PWA support: service worker and manifest (`public/sw.js`, `public/manifest.json`).

## 2) System design colors (mandatory)

### Source of truth
- The canonical app palette is defined in `src/theme/colors.ts` and must be treated as the single source of truth.
- Main design colors:
  - `primary`: `#F26076`
  - `secondary`: `#FF9760`
  - `accent`: `#458B73`
  - `warning`: `#FFD150`

### Compliance rules
- New UI work must use theme tokens from `src/theme/colors.ts` (or mapped Tailwind/theme tokens derived from it), not ad-hoc hex values.
- Do not replace these four main colors without an explicit design-system change request.
- If a new semantic color token is required, add it in `src/theme/colors.ts` first, then adopt it in UI.
- Keep contrast/readability requirements when applying brand colors to text, backgrounds, badges, and interactive states.

## 3) Role model and access model

### Roles
- `ADMIN`
- `STAFF`
- `CUSTOMER`

### Effective scoping rules in APIs
- `ADMIN`: full read/write across contracts and history (except endpoint-specific guards).
- `STAFF`: trainer-oriented scope (commonly by `sale_by` or `teach_by`) and limited lifecycle transitions.
- `CUSTOMER`: typically limited to contracts they purchased (`purchased_by === userInstantId`) and related sessions.

## 4) Core data model

### InstantDB entities
- `$users`
  - `email` unique/indexed optional
- `user_setting`
  - `role`, `clerk_id`, `first_name`, `last_name`
- `contract`
  - `created_at`, `updated_at`, optional `start_date`, optional `end_date`
  - `kind`: `PT | REHAB | PT_MONTHLY`
  - optional `credits`
  - `duration_per_session` (minutes): required per contract; integer, divisible by 15, min 15, max 180
  - `status`: contract lifecycle status
  - `money`, `sale_by`, `purchased_by`
- `history`
  - `date`, `from`, `to` (time-slot model)
  - `status`: history lifecycle status
  - `teach_by`
  - optional `user_check_in_time`, optional `staff_check_in_time`

### Links
- `contract` 1 -> many `history` via `historyContract`
- `history` many -> one `$users` via `historyUser` label `users`
- `user_setting` one -> one `$users` via `userSettings`
- `contract` one -> one `$users` via `contractUser` label `users`
- `contract` trainer link via `sale_by_user`
- `contract` customer link via `purchased_by_user`

### Derived fields and runtime semantics
- `contract.used_credits` is computed in `GET /api/contract/getAll` from history rows whose status is `NEWLY_CREATED` or `CHECKED_IN`.
- Credit availability checks in `POST /api/history/create` and `POST /api/contract/updateStatus` use the same `NEWLY_CREATED` + `CHECKED_IN` semantics.
- `isCompletedHistoryStatus()` is a completed-session helper for analytics/UI categorization and currently returns true only for `CHECKED_IN`.

## 5) Lifecycle state machines

### Contract statuses
`NEWLY_CREATED -> CUSTOMER_REVIEW -> CUSTOMER_CONFIRMED -> CUSTOMER_PAID -> PT_CONFIRMED -> ACTIVE -> EXPIRED`

Terminal side branch: `CANCELED`

#### Transition enforcement (`POST /api/contract/updateStatus`)
- `ADMIN`: can force any status.
- `STAFF`: only
  - `NEWLY_CREATED -> CUSTOMER_REVIEW`
  - `CUSTOMER_PAID -> PT_CONFIRMED`
- `CUSTOMER`: only
  - `CUSTOMER_REVIEW -> CUSTOMER_CONFIRMED`
  - `CUSTOMER_CONFIRMED -> CUSTOMER_PAID`
  - `PT_CONFIRMED -> ACTIVE`
- Non-admin cancel rules:
  - cannot cancel `ACTIVE`
  - cannot cancel already `CANCELED`/`EXPIRED`
  - customer can cancel only own purchased contracts
  - API allows cancel from `PT_CONFIRMED` for non-admin, but UI action buttons intentionally do not expose Cancel at `PT_CONFIRMED`

#### Contract action-button runtime behavior (`src/utils/statusUtils.ts`, `src/components/cards/ContractCard.tsx`)
- Action rendering requires `shouldShowContractActionButtons()`:
  - `ADMIN` and `STAFF`: can see action area for all contracts.
  - `CUSTOMER`: can see actions only when `contract.purchased_by === userInstantId`.
- Button generation source of truth is `getContractActionButtons()`:
  - `ADMIN`
    - `NEWLY_CREATED`: `Send to Customer`, `Cancel`
    - `CUSTOMER_REVIEW`: `Cancel`
    - `CUSTOMER_CONFIRMED`: `Cancel`
    - `CUSTOMER_PAID`: `PT Confirm Receipt`, `Cancel`
    - `PT_CONFIRMED`, `ACTIVE`, `CANCELED`, `EXPIRED`: no action buttons
  - `STAFF`
    - `NEWLY_CREATED`: `Send to Customer` and `Cancel`
    - `CUSTOMER_PAID`: `PT Confirm Receipt` and `Cancel`
    - `CUSTOMER_REVIEW`, `CUSTOMER_CONFIRMED`: `Cancel`
    - `PT_CONFIRMED`, `ACTIVE`, `CANCELED`, `EXPIRED`: no action buttons
  - `CUSTOMER`
    - `CUSTOMER_REVIEW`: `Confirm Details` and `Cancel`
    - `CUSTOMER_CONFIRMED`: `Payment Completed` and `Cancel`
    - `PT_CONFIRMED`: `Activate` only
    - `NEWLY_CREATED`, `ACTIVE`, `CANCELED`, `EXPIRED`: no action buttons
- Activation confirmation dialog appears when requested next status is `ACTIVE` and contract has both `start_date` and `end_date`, and current timestamp differs from `start_date`.

#### Auto-expire contract rules
- On contract list and status update paths, contracts may be auto-set to `EXPIRED` if:
  - pre-active status and `end_date < now`, or
  - status `ACTIVE` and no available credits (for `PT`/`REHAB`), where consumed credits are counted from history with status `NEWLY_CREATED` or `CHECKED_IN`

### History statuses
`NEWLY_CREATED -> CHECKED_IN`

Terminal side branches: `CANCELED`, `EXPIRED`

#### Check-in model (`POST /api/history/updateStatus`)
- Requested `CHECKED_IN` is dual-check-in workflow:
  - customer request sets `user_check_in_time`.
  - staff/admin request sets `staff_check_in_time`.
  - status stays `NEWLY_CREATED` until both timestamps exist; then status becomes `CHECKED_IN`.
- Duplicate side check-ins are blocked:
  - customer cannot set `user_check_in_time` twice.
  - staff/admin cannot set `staff_check_in_time` twice.
- Cancel behavior:
  - only sessions currently in `NEWLY_CREATED` can be canceled.
  - because first-side check-in keeps status as `NEWLY_CREATED`, cancel is still technically allowed until the session reaches `CHECKED_IN`.
- Auto-expire rule applies only to `NEWLY_CREATED` when session end time is in the past.

#### Session action-button runtime behavior (`src/utils/statusUtils.ts`, `src/components/cards/SessionCard.tsx`)
- Action visibility requires `shouldShowHistoryActionButtons()`:
  - `ADMIN` and `STAFF`: visible for all sessions.
  - `CUSTOMER`: visible only when session contract is owned by user.
- For `NEWLY_CREATED`, `getHistoryActionButtons()` provides `Cancel` for all roles.
- `SessionCard` separately renders a `Check-in` button for `NEWLY_CREATED` sessions:
  - customer can request check-in only when owner and `user_check_in_time` is empty.
  - staff/admin can request check-in only when `staff_check_in_time` is empty.
  - check-in button is disabled when caller side already checked in.
- For `CHECKED_IN`, `CANCELED`, and `EXPIRED`, no action buttons are rendered.

## 6) Functional flows by page

### `/` Dashboard (`src/app/(main)/page.tsx`)
- Requires signed-in user (redirect to `/sign-in` if not authenticated).
- Fetches user info, contracts, history.
- Shows quick stats:
  - active contracts count
  - upcoming sessions count
- Shows create-contract CTA for `ADMIN`/`STAFF`.
- Shows next sessions list and navigation to `/history`.

### `/contracts` (`src/app/(main)/contracts/page.tsx`)
- Role-aware list with infinite pagination via `useInfiniteContracts`.
- Filter drawer:
  - statuses multi-select
  - kind
  - contract-period date range (`start_date` maps to `contract.start_date >=`, `end_date` maps to `contract.end_date <=`)
  - role-dependent name search (`sale_by_name`, `purchased_by_name`)
- Member/CUSTOMER status-filter invariant:
  - `NEWLY_CREATED` must **not** appear in the status dropdown options.
  - Even if status query params are tampered, backend must still exclude `NEWLY_CREATED` for `CUSTOMER` role.
- Summary counts for total/active/pending/inactive.
- Create-contract modal available for `ADMIN`/`STAFF`.

#### Contract card identity display rules (`src/components/cards/ContractCard.tsx`)
- Customer display name derivation (`customerName`):
  - Source user link: first element of `contract.purchased_by_user`.
  - Source profile link: first element of `purchasedByUser.user_setting`.
  - Fallback order:
    - If `customerUserSetting` exists, build name from `[first_name, last_name]`, drop falsy values, then join with a single space.
    - If joined name is empty, fallback to `purchasedByUser.email`.
    - If email is missing, fallback to literal `Unknown Customer`.
    - If `customerUserSetting` is absent, use `purchasedByUser.email` first, otherwise `Unknown Customer`.
- Customer email derivation (`customerEmail`):
  - Uses `purchasedByUser.email`.
  - Falls back to `N/A` if missing.
- Sales rep display name derivation (`salesPerson`):
  - Source user link: first element of `contract.sale_by_user`.
  - Source profile link: first element of `saleByUser.user_setting`.
  - Fallback order:
    - If `salesUserSetting` exists, build name from `[first_name, last_name]`, drop falsy values, then join with a single space.
    - If joined name is empty, fallback to `saleByUser.email`.
    - If email is missing, fallback to literal `Unknown`.
    - If `salesUserSetting` is absent, use `saleByUser.email` first, otherwise `Unknown`.
- UI render mapping in card details block:
  - Customer label row renders `customerName` in the value text element.
  - Sales Rep label row renders `salesPerson` in the value text element.
  - Both value elements apply `truncate`, so long names/emails are visually clipped in-card.
- Contract action buttons in card use `getContractActionButtons()` from `src/utils/statusUtils.ts` as source of truth.
- Action button render gate uses `shouldShowContractActionButtons()`:
  - `ADMIN` and `STAFF` can see contract actions for all cards.
  - `CUSTOMER` can see actions only for own purchased contracts.
- Runtime button map:
  - `CUSTOMER_REVIEW`: `CUSTOMER` sees `Confirm Details`, `ADMIN/STAFF` see cancel-only.
  - `CUSTOMER_CONFIRMED`: `CUSTOMER` sees `Payment Completed`, `ADMIN/STAFF` see cancel-only.
  - `CUSTOMER_PAID`: `ADMIN/STAFF` see `PT Confirm Receipt` and cancel; `CUSTOMER` sees no action.
  - `PT_CONFIRMED`: only `CUSTOMER` sees `Activate`; `ADMIN` and `STAFF` see no action buttons.
- Create Session button behavior:
  - shown only when contract is `ACTIVE` and user is `ADMIN`/`STAFF`, or `CUSTOMER` owner.
  - for `PT`/`REHAB`, requires `used_credits < credits`; for `PT_MONTHLY`, credit-cap check is bypassed.

### `/history` (`src/app/(main)/history/page.tsx`)
- Infinite session list via `useInfiniteHistory`.
- Session categories/tabs:
  - upcoming
  - past
  - overdue
  - inactive
- Role-authenticated users can open create-session modal.
- Uses session temporal logic (`date + to*60*1000`) for categorization.
- Categorization rules:
  - upcoming: `NEWLY_CREATED` or `CHECKED_IN` whose end time has not passed.
  - past: `CHECKED_IN` whose end time has passed.
  - overdue: `NEWLY_CREATED` whose end time has passed.
  - inactive: `CANCELED` or `EXPIRED`.
- `SessionCard` actions are available only for `NEWLY_CREATED` and role/ownership-permitted users:
  - Check-in action participates in dual-check-in API semantics.
  - Cancel action calls `POST /api/history/updateStatus` with `CANCELED`.

### `/profile` (`src/app/(main)/profile/page.tsx`)
- Displays merged Clerk + user setting profile.
- Allows first/last name updates via `POST /api/user/updateBasicInfo`.
- Shows derived stats from contracts/history queries.
- Supports Clerk sign-out.

### `/sign-in` and `/offline`
- `/sign-in`: Clerk sign-in UI route.
- `/offline`: fallback page for PWA offline mode.

## 7) API contract map and special constraints

All route handlers typically set:
- `export const dynamic = 'force-dynamic'`
- `export const revalidate = 0`

### Contract APIs
- `POST /api/contract/create`
  - Roles: `ADMIN`, `STAFF`
  - Required: `kind`, `money`, `purchased_by`, `duration_per_session`
  - `duration_per_session` validation: integer, divisible by 15, min 15, max 180
  - Defaults: `status = NEWLY_CREATED`, `created_at = Date.now()`
  - Links trainer (`sale_by_user`) and customer (`purchased_by_user`)
- `POST /api/contract/update`
  - Role: `ADMIN` only
  - Requires `contract_id` and `duration_per_session`
  - `duration_per_session` validation: integer, divisible by 15, min 15, max 180
  - Partial field update for remaining fields; optional relink when `sale_by`/`purchased_by` changes
- `POST /api/contract/delete`
  - Role: `ADMIN` only
  - Soft delete by setting status `CANCELED`
- `GET /api/contract/getAll`
  - Role-scoped query
  - Supports pagination and filters: statuses, kind, date range, name keyword filters
  - Name filters resolve to user IDs by scanning `user_setting`
  - Computes `used_credits` from history statuses `NEWLY_CREATED` + `CHECKED_IN`
  - Auto-expires contracts in response path
  - Enforces customer visibility invariant by excluding `NEWLY_CREATED` contracts for `CUSTOMER` even when query params request it
- `POST /api/contract/updateStatus`
  - Role-based transition guard and cancellation guard
  - Auto-expire check before transition
  - Auto-expire-by-credits uses history statuses `NEWLY_CREATED` + `CHECKED_IN` for `PT`/`REHAB`
  - If activating and timestamp differs from existing `start_date`, shifts `start_date` to now and preserves duration by moving `end_date`

### History APIs
- `POST /api/history/create`
  - Role: all authenticated users with ownership rules
  - Requires: `contract_id`, `date`, `from`, `to`
  - Contract must be `ACTIVE`
  - Contract may auto-expire if ended
  - For `PT`/`REHAB`, verifies credits remaining using history statuses `NEWLY_CREATED` + `CHECKED_IN`
  - Enforces session duration rule: `(to - from)` must equal `contract.duration_per_session`
  - Legacy compatibility: if `contract.duration_per_session` is missing on old records, fallback expected duration is `90`
  - Enforces trainer schedule conflict check on same day and overlapping time range
  - Creates `NEWLY_CREATED` history, links contract and creator user
- `POST /api/history/update`
  - `ADMIN`: any history
  - `CUSTOMER`: only history of purchased contracts
  - Non-admin/non-customer path: creator-owned update check
  - Validates time range and conflict when schedule fields change
  - Enforces session duration rule: `(to - from)` must equal `contract.duration_per_session`
  - Legacy compatibility: if `contract.duration_per_session` is missing on old records, fallback expected duration is `90`
  - Blocks updates when contract not active or expired (and may auto-expire contract)
- `POST /api/history/delete`
  - Soft delete to `CANCELED`
  - Role checks similar to history update ownership model
- `GET /api/history/getAll`
  - Role-scoped retrieval:
    - admin all
    - staff by `teach_by`
    - customer by purchased contracts expansion
  - Supports filters: statuses, `start_date`, `end_date`
  - Auto-expires only `NEWLY_CREATED` past sessions
- `GET /api/history/getByContract`
  - Requires `contract_id`
  - Access by role and relation to contract
  - Auto-expires only `NEWLY_CREATED` past sessions
  - Returns sorted history newest-first
- `POST /api/history/updateStatus`
  - Status transition endpoint for cancel/check-in workflow
  - Enforces dual check-in semantics for `CHECKED_IN`
  - Allows cancel only when current status is `NEWLY_CREATED` (including partial check-in state)
  - Returns `last_check_in_by` as `CUSTOMER`, `STAFF`, or `ADMIN` when a check-in request succeeds
- `GET /api/history/getOccupiedTimeSlots`
  - Requires `user_id`, `date`
  - Returns active occupied ranges excluding `CANCELED` and `EXPIRED`
  - Used by scheduling UI via `useTrainerSchedule`

### User APIs
- `GET /api/user/getUserInformation`
  - Returns merged Clerk user + `user_setting` + `instantUser`
- `GET /api/user/checkUserSetting`
  - Returns existence flag and optional setting
- `POST /api/user/createUserSetting`
  - Creates default `CUSTOMER` role setting
  - Requires `first_name`, `last_name`
  - Links to existing `$users` by email
- `GET /api/user/getByRole`
  - Requester must be `ADMIN` or `STAFF`
  - Requires `role` query param
- `POST /api/user/updateBasicInfo`
  - Updates current user setting names

### Realtime APIs
- `GET /api/realtime/token`
  - Requires authenticated Clerk session
  - Resolves caller Instant user id from `user_setting.users[0].id`
  - Returns Ably token request scoped to subscribe-only capability for `user:{instantUserId}`
  - Used by `src/providers/RealtimeProvider.tsx` as `authUrl` for Ably client

## 8) Technical constraints and invariants

- Time-slot model:
  - `from` and `to` are numeric minute offsets (e.g. 480 = 08:00)
  - valid range requires `from < to`
  - session duration is contract-driven: `to - from === contract.duration_per_session`
  - contract duration must be integer, divisible by 15, and within [15, 180]
  - UI slot generation uses `duration_per_session` as step size; legacy contracts without this field use fallback `90`
- Session overlap rule:
  - conflict if `newFrom < existingTo && newTo > existingFrom`
  - ignores canceled and expired sessions
- Soft delete policy:
  - Contract/history delete endpoints cancel via status update, no hard delete
- Role resolution dependency:
  - Most APIs require `user_setting` existing and linked to an Instant `$users` row
- Cache behavior:
  - API handlers are forced dynamic; client cache managed by React Query invalidation
  - Cross-device cache refresh is event-driven: mutation APIs publish Ably events (`contract.changed`, `history.changed`) and subscribed clients invalidate contract/history query lists

## 9) Cleanup status (applied)

The previously tracked 9 inconsistency items have been aligned in code:

1. Occupied-slot API naming aligned in shared API types/hook usage (`GetOccupiedTimeSlots*`).
2. Stale missing-route references removed from active contracts/interfaces.
3. `GET /api/history/getOccupiedTimeSlots` now enforces Clerk auth + role checks.
4. Dashboard user shape now uses `instantUser?.[0]?.id` consistently.
5. `POST /api/contract/update` and `POST /api/history/update` now validate status enums strictly.
6. `GET /api/history/getAll` pagination now returns `total` as full filtered count.
7. Contract date filters now apply to contract period fields (`start_date`, `end_date`) instead of `created_at`.
8. Legacy completion fallback removed; only `CHECKED_IN` is counted as completed for completion analytics/category logic, while credit consumption currently uses `NEWLY_CREATED` + `CHECKED_IN`.
9. Rulebook and main docs were refreshed to match current runtime behavior.

## 10) Change checklist for future modifications

When changing any page, API, status, role rule, data field, or design token, update in same PR:

- This file `.cursor/rules/gochul-fitness-rules.mdc`
- `src/app/type/api/index.ts`
- Affected API route handlers under `src/app/api/**`
- Relevant hooks under `src/hooks/**`
- Relevant UI pages/components under `src/app/(main)/**` and `src/components/**`
- `src/theme/colors.ts` when color or design-token behavior changes

Do not merge behavior changes without synchronized rulebook updates.
